posts.body:
In the given code, the "out" animation is not being applied correctly.

The issue lies in the closeHandler function where the line this.addClassName(classes.out) is used. However, in functional components, the this keyword is not used. Instead, you can add the class directly to the element by manipulating the DOM.

Here's an updated version of the closeHandler function that adds the "out" class to the modal element:

javascript
Copy code
function closeHandler() {
  navigate("..");
  const modalElement = document.querySelector(`.${classes.modal}`);
  modalElement.classList.add(classes.out);
}
By using document.querySelector, we select the modal element based on the provided CSS class. Then, classList.add is used to add the "out" class to trigger the desired animation.
